            <h2>
                   <strong> Scholarship Description:</strong>
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                            Swami Dayanand Education Foundation Merit-cum-Means Scholarships 2018-19 invites applications from students pursuing Engineering, MBBS, IT, Pharmacy and Architecture courses in Government or private institutes in India. The key objective of the scholarship is to inspire and transform the lives of academically brilliant and economically backward students. The scholarship is being offered by Swami Dayanand Education Foundation. A total of 200 scholarships are being offered to students under the following categories: 
                            Smt. Shyam Lata Garg Scholarships - INR 50,000 per annumSh. Anand Swarup Garg Scholarships - INR 25,000 per annum Sh. Ram Lal Gupta Scholarships - INR 20,000 per annumSmt. Lilawanti Himatlal Desai Scholarships - INR 20,000Smt. Indira Jayendrakumar Shah - INR 20,000Smt. Shanti Devi Scholarships - INR 17,500 per annumSh. Ram Ji Lal Scholarships - INR 15,000 per annum
                            Note: 30% of the total scholarships are reserved for women candidates. <h2>
                                <hr>
                                    <strong>Eligibility for the Scholarship:</strong>
                                    </h2>
 <p>
 
To be eligible for this scholarship, an applicant must-
<ul>
<li>Be pursuing an MBBS, Engineering, IT, Pharmacy and Architecture course from a government or private institution in India by passing a competitive examination conducted by Central/State Board</li>
<li>Have gross annual family income less than INR 6 Lac from all sources  </li>
<li>Have secured 85% marks in class 12   </li>
<li> Have obtained minimum 25,000 rank in JEE (Main) or minimum 10,000 rank in JEE (Advanced) </li>
<li>Have obtained a Grade Point Average of at least 7.5 in 10 points scale system (for students in their second or third year of graduation program)  </li>
<li> Not be in receipt or intent to receive any other financial assistance/scholarship from any other source.  </li>
<strong>Note:</strong>The students who are getting reimbursement of tuition fees/fee waiver can apply for the scholarship. 
</ul>
</p>
