                                          </p>
                                            <h2>
                                                <hr>
                                                <strong>Documents required for the Scholarship: </strong>
                                                </h2>
                                                <pre>
•	Income certificate
•	Copy of class 10 and 12 mark sheets
•	Copy of rank card of entrance examination 
•	Copy of fee receipt submitted by the student or Admission Letter (for students who are taking admission this year)
•	Two recent passport size photograph, taken in last 6 months
•	Copy of ration card or ID proofs of parents
•	Certificate of family income/BPL certificate/ITR/Certificate from local panchayat office for proof of annual family income
•	Aadhaar ID or address proof

                                                        
                                                </pre>
                                                <h2>
                                                        <hr>
                                                          <strong>  Selection crteria:</strong>
                                                            </h2>
                                                            <p>
                                                                <ul><li>The scholars will be selected on the basis of their merit and family background such as the percentage of marks obtained in the course and annual income of the family.</li>
                                                                    <li>The preference will be given to students with lowest family income in the ascending order. </li>
                                                                    <li>The selection process involves two key stages </li>
                                                                    <li>Stage 1: Registration for Scholarship</li>
                                                                    <li>Stage 2: Submission of required documents of shortlisted candidates</li>
                                                                    </ul>


                                                            </p>
                                                                <h2>
                                                                        <hr>
                                                                        <strong>Terms and Condition: </strong>
                                                                        </h2>
                                                                        <p>
                                                                            <ul><li>The shortlisted candidates will be intimated through email or at the address mentioned in the form. </li>
                                                                                <li>Once the intimation is received, the shortlisted candidates are required to submit the detailed application along with the copies of required certificates. </li>
                                                                                <li>	The shortlisted candidates also have to submit an essay in  500 words on "About Challenges You Have Faced in Life and How You Have Responded to Them"</li>
                                                                                <li>The essay should be written either in Hindi or in their mother tongue. </li>
                                                                                <li>The scholarship amount will be paid in two instalments. </li>
                                                                                </p>

                                                
       
